1.name: bicycle
1.definition: a wheeled vehicle that has two wheels and is moved by foot pedals

2.name: car
2.definition: a motor vehicle with four wheels; usually propelled by an internal combustion engine

3.name: motorcycle
3.definition: a motor vehicle with two wheels and a strong frame

4.name: airplane
4.definition: an aircraft that has a fixed wing and is powered by propellers or jets

5.name: bus
5.definition: a vehicle carrying many passengers; used for public transport

6.name: train
6.definition: public transport provided by a line of railway cars coupled together and drawn by a locomotive

7.name: truck
7.definition: an automotive vehicle suitable for hauling

8.name: boat
8.definition: a small vessel for travel on water

9.name: traffic light
9.definition: a visual signal to control the flow of traffic at intersections

10.name: fire hydrant
10.definition: an upright hydrant for drawing water to use in fighting a fire

11.name: stop sign
11.definition: a sign visible from the street

12.name: parking meter
12.definition: a coin-operated timer located next to a parking space; depositing money into it entitles you to park your car there for a specified length of time

13.name: bench
13.definition: a long seat for more than one person

14.name: bird
14.definition: warm-blooded egg-laying vertebrates characterized by feathers and forelimbs modified as wings

15.name: cat
15.definition: feline mammal usually having thick soft fur and no ability to roar: domestic cats; wildcats

16.name: dog
16.definition: a member of the genus Canis (probably descended from the common wolf) that has been domesticated by man since prehistoric times; occurs in many breeds

17.name: horse
17.definition: solid-hoofed herbivorous quadruped domesticated since prehistoric times

18.name: sheep
18.definition: woolly usually horned ruminant mammal related to the goat

21.name: bear
21.definition: massive plantigrade carnivorous or omnivorous mammals with long shaggy coats and strong claws

22.name: zebra
22.definition: any of several fleet black-and-white striped African equines

23.name: giraffe
23.definition: tallest living quadruped; having a spotted coat and small horns and very long neck and legs; of savannahs of tropical Africa

24.name: backpack
24.definition: a bag carried by a strap on your back or shoulder

26.name: handbag
26.definition: a container used for carrying money and small personal items or accessories (especially by women)

27.name: tie
27.definition: neckwear consisting of a long narrow piece of material worn (mostly by men) under a collar and tied in knot at the front

28.name: suitcase
28.definition: a portable rectangular container for carrying clothes

29.name: frisbee
29.definition: a light, plastic disk about 10 inches in diameter; propelled with a flip of the wrist for recreation or competition

30.name: skis
30.definition: narrow wood or metal or plastic runners used in pairs for gliding over snow

31.name: snowboard
31.definition: a board that resembles a broad ski or a small surfboard; used in a standing position to slide down snow-covered slopes

32.name: sports ball
32.definition: round object that is hit or thrown or kicked in games

33.name: kite
33.definition: plaything consisting of a light frame covered with tissue paper; flown in wind at end of a string

34.name: baseball bat
34.definition: an implement used in baseball by the batter

35.name: baseball glove
35.definition: the handwear used by fielders in playing baseball

36.name: skateboard
36.definition: a board with wheels that is ridden in a standing or crouching position and propelled by foot

37.name: surfboard
37.definition: a narrow buoyant board for riding surf

38.name: tennis racket
38.definition: a racket used to play tennis

39.name: bottle
39.definition: a glass or plastic vessel used for storing drinks or other liquids; typically cylindrical without handles and with a narrow neck that can be plugged or capped

40.name: wine glass
40.definition: a glass that has a stem and in which wine is served

41.name: cup
41.definition: a small open container usually used for drinking; usually has a handle

42.name: fork
42.definition: cutlery used for serving and eating food

43.name: knife
43.definition: edge tool used as a cutting instrument; has a pointed blade with a sharp edge and a handle

44.name: spoon
44.definition: a piece of cutlery with a shallow bowl-shaped container and a handle; used to stir or serve or take up food

45.name: bowl
45.definition: a round vessel that is open at the top; used chiefly for holding food or liquids

46.name: banana
46.definition: any of several tropical and subtropical treelike herbs of the genus Musa having a terminal crown of large entire leaves and usually bearing hanging clusters of elongated fruits

47.name: apple
47.definition: fruit with red or yellow or green skin and sweet to tart crisp whitish flesh

48.name: sandwich
48.definition: two (or more) slices of bread with a filling between them

49.name: orange
49.definition: round yellow to orange fruit of any of several citrus trees

50.name: broccoli
50.definition: plant with dense clusters of tight green flower buds

51.name: carrot
51.definition: deep orange edible root of the cultivated carrot plant

52.name: hot dog
52.definition: a frankfurter served hot on a bun

53.name: pizza
53.definition: Italian open pie made of thin bread dough spread with a spiced mixture of e.g. tomato sauce and cheese

55.name: cake
55.definition: baked goods made from or based on a mixture of flour, sugar, eggs, and fat

56.name: chair
56.definition: a seat for one person, with a support for the back

57.name: couch
57.definition: an upholstered seat for more than one person

58.name: potted plant
58.definition: a plant suitable for growing in a flowerpot (especially indoors)

59.name: bed
59.definition: a piece of furniture that provides a place to sleep

60.name: dining table
60.definition: a table at which meals are served

61.name: toilet
61.definition: a plumbing fixture for defecation and urination

62.name: TV
62.definition: an electronic device that receives television signals and displays them on a screen

63.name: laptop
63.definition: a portable computer small enough to use in your lap

64.name: mouse
64.definition: a hand-operated electronic device that controls the coordinates of a cursor on your computer screen as you move it around on a pad; on the bottom of the device is a ball that rolls on the surface of the pad

65.name: remote
65.definition: a device that can be used to control a machine or apparatus from a distance

66.name: keyboard
66.definition: device consisting of a set of keys on a piano or organ or typewriter or typesetting machine or computer or the like

67.name: cell phone
67.definition: telephony that uses transmission by radio rather than by wire

68.name: microwave
68.definition: kitchen appliance that cooks food by passing an electromagnetic wave through it; heat results from the absorption of energy by the water molecules in the food

69.name: oven
69.definition: kitchen appliance used for baking or roasting

70.name: toaster
70.definition: a kitchen appliance (usually electric) for toasting bread

71.name: sink
71.definition: plumbing fixture consisting of a water basin fixed to a wall or floor and having a drainpipe

72.name: refrigerator
72.definition: white goods in which food can be stored at low temperatures

73.name: book
73.definition: a written work or composition that has been published (printed on pages bound together)

74.name: clock
74.definition: a timepiece that shows the time of day

75.name: vase
75.definition: an open jar of glass or porcelain used as an ornament or to hold flowers

76.name: scissors
76.definition: an edge tool having two crossed pivoting blades

77.name: teddy bear
77.definition: plaything consisting of a child's toy bear (usually plush and stuffed with soft materials)

78.name: hair drier
78.definition: a hand-held electric blower that can blow warm air onto the hair; used for styling hair

79.name: toothbrush
79.definition: small brush; has long handle; used to clean teeth
